-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.7","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for contracts, schema examples, and registry discovery logic","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the contract layer and discovery layer so the robot model stays explicit and machine-consumable. This task exists because schema/versioning rules, example payloads, surface metadata, and discovery output are easy to erode if only exercised indirectly by broader tests.","design":"The tests should cover schema ID and versioning rules, required or optional or empty field semantics, deterministic ordering requirements, normative example payload validation, truncation and pagination metadata semantics, action-handoff and remediation-hint shapes, request identity or idempotency rules, operator attention-state rules, recoverable error semantics, explainability and evidence shapes, aggregation or suppression metadata semantics, diagnostic discovery output, scenario or example drift detection, capabilities/help/schema discovery output, replacement or removal markers where relevant, and registry metadata consistency. They should be table-driven, live beside the implementation in _test.go files, and log scenario names, schema IDs, section names, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, suppression markers, error codes, diagnostic handles, and high-signal diffs when assertions fail.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when contracts, checked-in examples, and registry or discovery logic have deterministic unit coverage for happy-path, edge-case, and error-case behavior with detailed logging suitable for debugging drift quickly, including retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-override semantics.","notes":"If a future contract change can silently alter discovery or field semantics without a noisy unit-test failure, this task is incomplete.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:47.707037882Z","creat